The position of Senator was created to represent the interests of the State and through that the best interests of the people as part of the Ohio Compromise when the delegates drafted the constitution to limit democracy while providing more power to the federal government after Shay's Rebellion involving 4000 veterans of the American Revolutionary War. Initially, the two senstors were either appointed by the Governor of the State or the State Legislature and not elected by the populace. The House of Representatives was created to represent the interests of the populace or the people and have always been directly elected by the people. The needs, desires and interests of the people can often be at odds with those of the state and some of the delegates were afraid the larger, more populous states would dominate the less populous states. Business interests within a state will always take priority with the Senstors over those of the general populace when they are at odds with one another. To compromise, and ensure neither the state nor rhe populace was subject to the tyranny of the other, all bills must be passed by both chambers.

Now that the populace votes for the senator along with their representatives, there should be more incentive for the senator to keep the interests of the populace closer to being equal with the interests of the state. Unfortunately, once elected to either the house or the senate, the elected official has an incredibly high statistical chance of keeping their seat because of name recognition and the higher campaign contributions they earn from the businesses who's interests they serve which makes it nearly impossible to unseat them.
